	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=16450&amp;mid=103560066018692">RE: suck</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=16450&amp;mid=103560066018692#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Fri, Oct 25th 11:10 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=65101"><span id="Scholar">Drienne</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">294 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Excellent [4.80]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>In outdoor zones, a Ranger would be better off just pulling with a bow and not snaring, for several reasons.&nbsp;&nbsp;Firstly, you can hit things much, much farther away with a bow than with a spell (even with Extended Range, which increases by only 15%).  Secondly, snaring a mob to run back to camp can be a bit counter-productive.  If you get too far away from the mob, it loses interest and wanders away.  And if you have to stay close enough to maintain aggro, you have a greater chance of adds (you have to move slower back to camp, giving you more time to run into something).</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76285 target=akztarg>Drienne Gardairne</a> -- 68 Ranger<br/><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=316502 target=akztarg>Xide Kyck</a> -- 65 Necromancer<br/><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=725442 target=akztarg>Hwel Jung</a> -- 65 Rogue</td></tr>
